	   <tr><td colspan=2>&gt;I mean, WTF man? All you have to do is the /pet back off command until your pet backs off. If it doesn't work once, then KEEP DOING IT!!! and your pet will back off. <br><br>Ok, two questions.<br><br>First, if a pet gets hit, will it or will it not hit back even if previously backed off?<br><br>Second, if a mob has been hit by a pet and no other action has been taken that earns more hate, will it or will it not continue hitting the pet?<br><br>My impression is yes to both questions.  So, you've got a mob that's hitting your pet, and you've got your pet that keeps retaliating.  Why would /pet back off ever work?  If you "KEEP DOING IT!!!," the mob will KEEP hitting your pet, and your pet will KEEP getting started hitting it again.  <br><br>If a mez lands at a moment when the laggy system decides that a /pet back off has just landed, great.  If a mez lands at a moment when the laggy system decides a blow from the mob has just landed, the pet would be very likely to hit once before the next /pet back off works its way through cyberspace to the server.  <br><br>Then, if things work the way I think they do, you would have a backed-off pet, a woken-up mob, and a ticked-off dead enchanter.<br><br>So in one sense, you're right: it would get the pet backed off eventually.  But what I was really asking was whether there was a way of backing a pet off from a mob that's still hitting it, *before* the mob gets aggroed onto your cleric or enchanter.<br><br>I've never had an enchanter volunteer to die in the name of science and let me test this out, so I don't really know for sure.  (My RL brother's primary is a druid, so I've spent a lot of time hunting giants and other outdoor kite fodder, so my time in groups based on enchanter crowd control has been limited.)  But as I level, I'm more and more likely to be in that situation. So far, I've always just been careful not to let my pet get aggroed on by part of a big pull, to the point of not summoning one if there's no place to keep them out of combat until things are under control.  <br> <br>&nbsp;<br>Necro 40 of Nighthaven<br>on Cazic-Thule</td></tr>
