	   <tr><td colspan=2>'/pet back off' just isn't going to work if you are soloing. There are only two things for the mob to hit (you and the pet) and your pet is going to attack the mob if either one of you takes a hit. That's its job, and 99% of the time, you'll be thankful for that.<br><br>In a group setting, tell your pet not to taunt, and wait until the main tank is fully engaged with the main pull before sending in your pet. If you've got a good tank in your gruop, he's hitting "Taunt" every time the button pops up. That's his main job.<br><br>If the pull starts getting a little nasty, maybe you don't have a healer or the healer is out of mana and the tank is low on health, have the tank back up and tell your pet to start taunting. Your group now has a new tank.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
