	   <tr><td colspan=2>Keep in mind that the BIG difference between /pet sit and /pet guard here   is this<br><br>SIT:   pet stays while you run.. if you get attacked it comes to assist you.. when the fight is over the pet will sit right where it is and not move..  (can be good and bad.. specifically in dungeons)<br><br>Guard Here:  Pet stays while you run.. if you get attacked it comes to assist you.. when fight is over the pet will RETURN to the spot you told him to guard.  VERY useful in outside areas where you may be moving around pulling etc.. or if you get annoyed with your pet always "in your face".<br><br>I'm beginning to appreciate SIT now that you can summon your pet if it isnt agro'ed..<br><br>good luck<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
