	   <tr><td colspan=2>Have a question, and I hope a number of you will take the time to seriously check into this and help me verify what I've found, or disprove me. =) Either way we'd all benefit.<br><br>When comparing stats on various mage gear I'll notice tradeoffs such as 1 less INT but +10 or +20 mana. And I ask myself, which is more valuable? The extra point of INT, or the straight up mana?<br><br>The two robes I'm comparing for this question are the Blackened Crystalline Robe and the advisors robe. and the stats for both can be found by searching the equimpent area of the web site.<br><br>My findings so far:<br><br>When I used the mana calc on eq.castersrealm I found that the 1 point of INT at lvl 60 yeilded only 18 mana, and thus the one less point of INT and +20 mana would SEEM to be superior. If that's the case then, why dont we all run out and grab advisors robes? They're comin down in price.<br><br>Granted the Blackend Robe is more chanter oriented, it looks DAMN good on me. Thus I ask this question. Which is better?<br><br>Please post feedback, adn feel free to throw up numbers around, as long as it isn't fuzzy math I'm sure we'd all be happy to take a look.<br><br>Thanks in advance,<br><br>Klateau Beratanektu<br>Mage of Innoruuk<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
