<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98433424293439></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98433424293439><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=12&mid=98433424293439>Getting the Level 16 and 20 pet spells</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?id=21128><span id= >Beetlebrow</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>53 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sun, Mar 11th 1:10 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.45]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Kadthar here,<br><br>This will be a long post.  I'm going to describe exactly how I went through getting the pet spells for Levels 16 and 20.  This comes from the perspective of an Erudite magician or a human magician starting out of Qeynos, so if you're a high elf, dark elf, or gnome, or a human out of Freeport, the process can be much simplified.<br>First, I started from Qeynos. If you're on Odus, the trip to Qeynos is only a quick boat ride, so it shouldn't be a big deal to start out your trip there.  The first thing you'll need to do is get to Highpass.  There is another way through, but I believe it would be more difficult.  Getting to Higpass is pretty simple, though, particularly if you're invisible.  You pass through Qeynos Hills, West Karana, North Karana and East Karana on the way there.  This trip is not too difficult to find your way through....you need to follow the paths and the sign markers which will direct you to Highpass.  You should definitely be invisible through North and East Karana if you're Level 16 or about, though it's probably a good idea to be invisible in West Karana, too, just to make sure that none of the few dangerous creatures there bother you.  The only place where there will be any question of which way to go is in West Karana, as there are several intersections on the path to North Karana, not all of which have a path marker.  Most (if not all) of the alternate paths will be dead ends eventually, leading either to one of the various farms, bandit camps, or in one case, to the ogre camp.  This is the one you particularly want to avoid as some of the ogres see invisible creatures.  When the path forks near the two-spawn bandit spot in the road, take the direction where the bandits spawn.  The other way will lead to the ogres.  Otherwise, as long as you're invisible, you should be safe, even if you mistakenly choose the wrong path.<br>Once you've gone through the Karanas, and have arrived in Highpass, I suggest you bind yourself there as I did.  It is a better place to come back to if you die further on than going back all the way to Qeynos.  This is particularly important at this point as you're nearing Freeport and have to pass through Kithicor to get there.  Again, it's absolutely essential to be invisible when going through Kithicor as it is a dangerous zone.  Furthermore, I had been warned to only travel there during the day.  I followed this warning and that is probably the reason I got through the whole trip without dying.  Go past the orc camp in Highpass and from there you will enter Kithicor.  It is a good idea to be invisible even while in Highpass, as the orc camp will cause you problems if you aren't.  When you go into Kithicor if it is day, and early enough that you don't feel that you'll have night fall on you in the forest, you can travel the zone safely by remaining invisible and hugging the zone wall. (Ideally, you'll want to remain high on the wall.)  If it is night, wait invisible near the zone border (or in Highpass preferably) until day breaks.  Hug the right wall as you come out of Highpass and keep going until you reach the entrance to West Commons.  The only creature I saw while I was in the zone during the day was the leader of the Shralok orcs, and he didn't see me.  Once you're in West commons, follow the north wall (the left wall) into East commons and from there continue to follow the same wall into Freeport.  In West Commons, there is one undead camp on the wall you'll want to avoid....I suppose it's best to avoid all the camps, which you can do quite easily if you're invisible.  There is one zone entrance on this wall in East commons, into Nektulos, but you'll ignore it.<br>Now that you're in West Freeport, you'll need to go into East Freeport and catch the boat into the Ocean of Tears.  This is the point that humans from Freeport will start their journey, a much shorter one.  Also, once a dark elf sneaks into Freeport after traveling through Nektulos and East Commons, he or she will start the journey here as well.  Gnomes and High Elves will have to ride the boat to Freeport from Butcherblock, but there is no need to actually stop in Freeport, as any mage needs to catch the boat here to get these spells.  There may be a long wait for the boat to arrive, but after catching it, the ride will be short.  You will need to ride the boat into the Ocean of Tears, and get off on the first island, which is called Sister Island.  This is where the trip becomes a problem for dark elves, though all other races (depending possibly upon religion) should be fine all the way through.  Travel along the coast of Sister Island to the right, also invisible here, until you get to a dwarven camp.  The invisibility is necessary here as there are some unfriendly pirates roaming the island.  From the dwarf camp, swim out to an island that should be visible here, with a tower on it.  At this tower is the high elf merchant that sells your Level 16 and 20 pet spells, along with various other magician spells.  Invisibility is good here, also, as there is a cyclops on this island that will probably eat you if he sees you.  Since your invisibility will drop when you purchase the spells, it is a good idea to have your sound up when you get to this island as the thumping noise will warn you when the cyclops in near.  Purchasing these spells is also a problem for dark elves, or so I've heard, and could be for others depending on religion and other faction issues.  Once you've purchased your pet spells, the easiest way to make the return trip is to gate back to whatever safe bind point you left from, unless there is some hunting you want to do in the Ocean of Tears.  Of course, that will probably involve some swimming as the boat trips are rather infrequent and involve long waits here.<br>Well, that's the way I made the trip.  I hope that it is of some use to some of you.  Sorry about the huge length of the post.<br><br>Kadthar<br>Level 18 Erudite Gatecaller (Magician) &lt;Divinity&gt;<br>Tholuxe Paells<br><br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
