	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Mar 8th 5:29 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>While I agree with the majority of the post, I believe the 8 to 20 should be changed. From lvl 8 to 12 you can solo the thugs, smugglers in the Qeynos sewers. This zone gives a 20% bonus to XP. You should be able to solo the thugs at 8. These are on a 5 min spawn so you have time to med to full then nuke. At 12 you should be able to handle 2 of the Smuggler spawns. Loot is decent with the ocassional Bronze drop. At 12 to 16 Hunt bandits in the WK. The 2 spawn bandits on the road is great for soloing. These drop bronze weapons and the red sash. Fill up you summoned bags with bronze weapons and sashes. Gate back to (Qeynos you did bind there ?) Sell the bronze and turn int the sashes to the pally next to the shield salesman. He gives xp and some gold and Bronze weapons. A 2 hour camp of the spawn netted me a level and 60pp. I turned in 14 sashes. Farmers at the barn with the bandits always drop sashes and are green to a lvl 12. This is better than Wisps because it cuts down all the travel time on the boat and the long run back and forth to turn in the GLstones.<br><br>16 to 20 ORCS<br>Since you just had to go to the OOT to get your pet spells, stop in the oasis to lvl to 18. Good loot dropped and the orc highway there means little down time. 18 to 20 run to HHP and hunt the orc spawn there. This spawn is also very fast and the orcs drop bronze weapons and ringmail armor. The orc spawn is also right next to the zone line for quick evac and a bank is in the next zone HHK.<br>&nbsp;<br>Shoikan Shonuff<br>40 DE SK<br>Rodcent Nife</td></tr>
