	   <tr><td colspan=2>Make a /pet back off hot key.<br><br>When you send your pet in, if it is not going to a target that you would like it to, hit your back off key.<br><br>I find that sending in a spell first, will alow you to bring your mob into a selected area of your choice.<br><br>As it gets closer, make sure you hit pet follow me.<br>Run backwards to be able to view the mob coming at you.<br>Once you are in a safe area that will not cause other mobs to gang up on you, send your pet in.<br><br>By doing this you will be able to keep out of the agro area, and you will allways know what mob you are dealing with.<br><br>This is how I solo Aviaks.<br>We all know that the Aviaks can get totaly agro.<br>So we must seperate them out of the agro area.<br><br>If you are in trouble, you will be far enough from the agro area to see what's comming at you.<br>Send your pet in with a fire shield, and blast away.<br>If you are being ganged up on, and you have allready sent the pet in and you can take a few hits.<br><br>Help kill what the pet is holding, use the back off hot key, and send it after the new mob.<br><br>Allways check your pets health it's the most important part of fighting with a pet.<br><br>Build a hot key to kill your pet.<br>If I'm not mistaken it is /pet go away or /pet begone.<br><br>I'm sorry but I cant remember and I am at work so I can't look at my hot keys :-)<br><br>Or you can use the reclaim energy spell.<br>(But that will cost a little mana)<br>(But it will give a little mana back and also kill your pet)<br><br>Once your pet is down to almost dead.<br>Cast another pet spell, and right before it finsishes the last bubble of the cast, kill your pet and send the new one in.<br>This takes practice, but it can be done.<br><br>It will save you in the event that you need to runaway, and you know that another spell would not kill the mob.<br>This way your pet will distract it for just enough time for you to get away, or possibly finish off the job that the other pet could not finsh.<br><br>Allways make sure you have the strongest pet when you con it.<br>If you dont you will spend more time healing your pet and doing corpse runs.<br><br>If you are on the Rathe server, look me up.<br><br>Revolt 21 Mage (Guardians of the Fathe)The Rathe<br>Zoidicus 12 Enc The Rathe<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
